{"action":"created","issue":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/54427","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/54427/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/54427/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/54427/events","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/issues/54427","id":2289339377,"node_id":"I_kwDOABkWpM6IdIvx","number":54427,"title":"make `Base.@assume_effects :nothrow` mark throwing expressions as `unreachable`","user":{"login":"nsajko","id":4944410,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ5NDQ0MTA=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/4944410?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/nsajko","html_url":"https://github.com/nsajko","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nsajko/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nsajko/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nsajko/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nsajko/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nsajko/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nsajko/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nsajko/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nsajko/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nsajko/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":115858,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwxMTU4NTg=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/labels/performance","name":"performance","color":"d7e102","default":false,"description":"Must go faster"}],"state":"open","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2024-05-10T09:14:55Z","updated_at":"2024-05-10T13:35:50Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"This would provide a pure-Julia way to implement an assumed-unreachable statement, and thus fix #52851 without introducing any new features. Also xref #51729. If this were implemented, any statement that's annotated with `Base.@assume_effects :nothrow`, but statically known to throw would be equivalent to `unreachable()`. E.g., `7::Union{}` would be assumed unreachable.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/54427/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/54427/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null},"comment":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/comments/2104623960","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/issues/54427#issuecomment-2104623960","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/54427","id":2104623960,"node_id":"IC_kwDOABkWpM59cgNY","user":{"login":"mikmoore","id":95002244,"node_id":"U_kgDOBamehA","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/95002244?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikmoore","html_url":"https://github.com/mikmoore","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikmoore/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikmoore/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikmoore/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikmoore/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikmoore/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikmoore/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikmoore/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikmoore/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikmoore/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2024-05-10T13:35:49Z","updated_at":"2024-05-10T13:35:49Z","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"This is a clever way to implement unreachable, but I don't like it. It's too hard to use properly. An `unreachable()` function or macro seems to be a much safer and more ergonomic implementation.

`Base.@assume_effects` is annotated at the function level. This makes it too coarse-grained to use responsibly for this purpose. A `:nothrow` annotation like this would also seem to risk applying recursively to any functions called (or at least to inlined functions), which makes this dangerous in the first place and a maintenance nightmare if any of those called functions ever change.

I think we shouldn't have this for many of the same reasons we don't have global `@fastmath` (any more).","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/comments/2104623960/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null}}

