On version 1.8.0 (sorry it's what i have handy, but the offending method appears unchanged on current `master`):
```julia-repl
julia> using BenchmarkTools

julia> x = 1; y = 2:2;

julia> @btime vcat($x, $x);
  26.506 ns (1 allocation: 80 bytes)

julia> @btime vcat($y, $y);
  28.744 ns (1 allocation: 80 bytes)

julia> @btime vcat($x, $y);
  2.667 μs (35 allocations: 1.05 KiB)
```
with similar results for `hcat`.

An initial inspection suggests that the offending methods are `LinearAlgebra._vcat(A::Union{Number, LinearAlgebra.UniformScaling, AbstractVecOrMat}...; array_type)` and the matching `_hcat`, which are (as of this writing) defined at [uniformscaling.jl#L426](https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/blob/master/stdlib/LinearAlgebra/src/uniformscaling.jl#L426). A loop over the input vararg tuple appears to cause dynamic dispatch.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/48850/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/48850/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}}

