julia> @btime vcat($x, $y);
  43.897 ns (1 allocation: 80 bytes)
```

The issue was that in Base the concatenation methods are completely generic, and that the methods in uniformscaling.jl are pirating the case when only a vecormat and numbers are present. This resolves the ambiguity, and simplifies the case where both uniform scalings _and_ numbers are present. In that case, the scalings can only have size 1x1, or, equivalently, be numbers.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/48933/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/48933/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null},"comment":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/comments/1458324286","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/48933#issuecomment-1458324286","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/48933","id":1458324286,"node_id":"IC_kwDOABkWpM5W7EM-","user":{"login":"mikmoore","id":95002244,"node_id":"U_kgDOBamehA","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/95002244?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikmoore","html_url":"https://github.com/mikmoore","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikmoore/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikmoore/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikmoore/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikmoore/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikmoore/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikmoore/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikmoore/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikmoore/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mikmoore/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2023-03-07T15:01:09Z","updated_at":"2023-03-07T15:01:09Z","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"Another possibility might be to change the existing `UniformScaling` methods to use `map(szfun,A)` where `szfun(::UniformScaling) = -1` and `szfun(x::Any) = size(x,$dim)` for the appropriate dimension. I.e., the same as it is now, but use a `map` over the inhomogeneous `A::Tuple` instead of a loop over it. Then all the unstable loops over `A` could be changed to loops over the resulting `NTuple{N,Int}`. This would resolve the instability even when `UniformScaling` are present.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/comments/1458324286/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null}}

